# AI-Assisted-Motor-Claims-Automation-Platform
This repository documents my end-to-end product thinking for designing an AI-assisted motor claims automation platform for insurers in Southeast Asia.

## Overview
This repository documents my end-to-end product thinking for designing an AI-assisted motor claims automation platform for insurers in Southeast Asia.

The focus is not on code, but on:
- Problem discovery
- Product decisions and trade-offs
- MVP scoping
- Metrics and outcomes

## Problem Statement
Motor claims processing is slow, manual, and error-prone.

Current challenges observed:
- Average claims turnaround time (TAT): 7–14 days
- High dependency on human assessors
- Fraud and overpayment leakage
- Poor policyholder experience due to lack of transparency

## Target Users
- Claims Officers
- Claims Managers
- Policyholders
- External Adjusters (optional)


## Product Goal
Reduce motor claims turnaround time by **40% within 6 months** while maintaining fraud detection accuracy.

## Solution Summary
An AI-assisted claims triage and processing platform that:
- Automates document intake and validation
- Uses rules + AI to classify claims
- Flags suspicious claims for human review
- Provides real-time status updates to policyholders

## Scope
✅ In scope:
- Motor claims only
- Document-based claims
- Rule-based + AI-assisted triage

❌ Out of scope:
- Medical claims
- Full fraud investigation
- Core policy administration replacement

## What This Case Study Demonstrates
- Structured problem framing
- Clear trade-offs
- MVP-first mindset
- Comfort working with technical constraints
